==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monotype
<hw>Mon"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Monotype
<hw>Mon"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> +
<ets>-type</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The only
representative of its group, as a single species constituting a
genus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A print (but one impression can be taken) made by
painting on metal and then transferring the painting to paper by
pressure; also, the process of making such prints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of keyboard-operated typesetting and casting
machine that makes and sets separate characters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monovalent</ent>⟦br⟧
